      {
        "id": "5ed7614c6dfb1eb51122634a25b12bc561d19479",
        "author": {
          "account_id": 1077,
          "name": "Michael O'Brien",
          "display_name": null,
          "email": "frank.obrien@amdocs.com",
          "username": "michaelobrien"
        },
        "author_role": "OWNER",
        "timestamp": "2018-08-29 22:19:19.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 2:\n\nChart.yaml would have worked - but in the end the helm-verify job was not seeing any changes - only merged master - raised LF ticket (hence no merge would have fixed this until Mandeep snuck in a change before the jobbuilder put a -1\n\nPrudence Au, Mandeep and I triaged this.\n\n \n\nThere were 2 issues\n\nThe oom-master-verify-helm job (new) does not cherry-pick changes – it runs directly from master prior to merges\n(note that this helm verify job is new from last week – there have not been a lot of merge testing – so this is part of verification testing in a way)\nThe effect of this is that a helm-verify job that should fail – does not – later the master-merge-helm job fails\nAny attempt to fix the build can only be done in the small window before the jobbuilder (verify-helm) runs and puts a -1 on the review\n(Mandeep did one of these for us)\n\nThe copyright symbol caused issues in the make job inside of the helm verify job\nRemoving the symbol (in this case) worked locally but required the quick slip under the jobbuilder to get a +1\nCopying the CR symbol from another helm chart also worked\n \n\nFix required:\n\nTODO: The verify-helm job needs to be adjusted so that it picks up the review instead of running only on the merged master branch",
        "patchset_number": 2
      }
    ]
